State MSM Profile: Massachusetts

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Massachusetts

An estimated 111,625 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Massachusetts in 2013, representing 2.5% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 2,477,594 adult men of Massachusetts, 4.5% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was greater than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Massachusetts resided in fringe counties of large metropolitan areas (59.7%). Including both central and fringe counties, 83.3% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Massachusetts, 2013

MSM in Massachusetts Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Massachusetts, Middlesex County had the largest population of MSM at 28,121, representing 25.2% of all MSM in the state. Suffolk County had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Massachusetts at 9.1%. This was greater than the percentage for Massachusetts as a whole, which was 4.5% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Massachusetts Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Boston-Cambridge-Newton Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Boston-Cambridge-Newton MSA overlaps two states: Massachusetts and New Hampshire. The Massachusetts portion of the MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Massachusetts at 85,724, or 76.8% of all MSM in the state and 92.6% of the 92,527 MSM in the MSA. Of the 1,569,343 adult men in the Massachusetts part of Boston-Cambridge-Newton, an estimated 5.5% were MSM. This was greater than the percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA as a whole, which was 5.3% of adult men (92,527 out of 1,729,903).



Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Worcester Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Worcester MSA overlaps two states: Connecticut and Massachusetts. The Massachusetts portion of the MSA had 8,044 MSM, or 7.2% of all MSM in the state and 89.0% of the 9,037 MSM in the MSA. Of 301,082 adult men in the Massachusetts part of Worcester, 2.7% were MSM. This was greater than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 2.6% of adult men (9,037 out of 346,199).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Providence-Warwick Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Providence-Warwick MSA overlaps two states: Massachusetts and Rhode Island. The Massachusetts portion of the MSA had 7,221 MSM, or 6.5% of all MSM in the state and 23.3% of the 31,036 MSM in the MSA. Of 204,730 adult men in the Massachusetts part of Providence-Warwick, 3.5% were MSM. This was less than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 5.2% of adult men (31,036 out of 600,635).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Springfield Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Springfield MSA had a population of 5,335 MSM, or 4.8% of all MSM in Massachusetts. Of the 229,558 adult men in Springfield, an estimated 2.3% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Barnstable Town Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Barnstable Town MSA had a population of 2,946 MSM, or 2.6% of all MSM in Massachusetts. Of the 84,090 adult men in Barnstable Town, an estimated 3.5% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Pittsfield Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Pittsfield MSA had a population of 1,158 MSM, or 1.0% of all MSM in Massachusetts. Of the 50,289 adult men in Pittsfield, an estimated 2.3% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
